  "texts": [
    "A lower value is specified for shorter responses and a higher value for potentially longer responses.",
    "OpenAI LLMs (see Section 3.3), through their API, offer a parameter that specifies the number of responses that the model should return in a single request, and the user is only charged for the extra tokens of the extra output cases.",
    "A prompt is an NL text describing the task that an LLM should perform.",
    "Prompts are used to interact and instruct models.",
    "An LLM works to predict the next best group of letters, called \"tokens\", from the prompt."
